# Detecta Core — AI Coding Rules
# For Cursor, Copilot, Windsurf, and other LLM-assisted editors.

## Stack
- React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Edge Functions, Realtime, Storage)
- TanStack Query v5 for server state
- react-router-dom v6 for routing
- NO Next.js, NO SSR, NO Angular/Vue/Svelte
- NO backend server code (Python, Node, Ruby) — all server logic in Supabase Edge Functions

## Architecture Reference
- Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` in project root for full structure, hooks, and domain map.

## Imports
- ALWAYS use `@/` alias for absolute imports: `import { X } from '@/components/...'`
- Supabase client: `import { supabase } from '@/integrations/supabase/client'`
- Roles/access: `import { ADMIN_ROLES, ... } from '@/constants/accessControl'`
- Role types: `import { Role } from '@/types/roleTypes'`
- DO NOT create new Supabase client instances

## Security — CRITICAL
- Roles MUST be stored in `user_roles` table — NEVER on `profiles` table
- NEVER check auth/roles via localStorage, sessionStorage, or hardcoded credentials
- Server-validated role: `supabase.rpc('get_current_user_role_secure')`
- All data access must respect RLS (Row Level Security) policies
- Role lists must come from `src/constants/accessControl.ts` — never hardcode in components
- Use `RoleProtectedRoute` or `RoleBlockedRoute` for route-level access control
- Field operators (custodio, armado, instalador) have dedicated portals and CANNOT access admin modules

## Data Fetching
- Use `useAuthenticatedQuery()` from `@/hooks/useAuthenticatedQuery` for authenticated queries
- Use `supabase.rpc()` for complex queries, aggregations, and security-sensitive operations
- Use `supabase.from('table').select()` for simple CRUD
- TanStack Query for ALL server state — no Redux, no Zustand, no global stores
- Choose query config: 'standard' (30s), 'static' (10min), 'critical' (10s + auto-refetch)

## UI Components
- Use shadcn/ui for ALL base components (Button, Dialog, Card, Input, Select, etc.)
- DO NOT create custom base components that duplicate shadcn functionality
- Use Tailwind semantic tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`, etc.
- NEVER hardcode colors (no `text-white`, `bg-black`, `text-blue-500` in components)
- All colors defined as CSS variables in `src/index.css` using HSL format
- Framer Motion is NOT installed — use CSS transitions or Tailwind animate classes

## Mobile Responsiveness
- ALWAYS check `useIsMobile()` from `@/hooks/use-mobile` when building UI
- Mobile: compact pills, stacked cards, bottom sheets, smaller padding
- Desktop: full tables, side-by-side layouts, larger spacing
- Every new page/component MUST be responsive

## Forms
- Use react-hook-form + zod for validation
- Use shadcn/ui Form components

## File Organization
- Hooks: `src/hooks/use[Entity].ts` — one hook per file
- Pages: `src/pages/[Module]/` — PascalCase folder, index.tsx entry
- Components: `src/components/[domain]/[ComponentName].tsx`
- Keep components small and focused — extract sub-components when > 200 lines

## Edge Functions
- Located in `supabase/functions/[name]/index.ts`
- Deno runtime, TypeScript
- Standard CORS headers pattern
- Always validate auth token in function body

## Key Files to Read First
- `src/constants/accessControl.ts` — role-based access control (SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH)
- `src/types/roleTypes.ts` — all role definitions
- `src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` — auth provider
- `src/App.tsx` — all route definitions
- `src/index.css` — design tokens and CSS variables
- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — full architecture documentation

## Business Domain
- This is a security/logistics operations platform (armed custody, GPS monitoring, escort services)
- "Servicio" = custody service, "Custodio" = custody agent, "Armado" = armed guard
- "Instalador" = GPS installer, "C5" = monitoring center, "SIERCP" = risk evaluation
- Spanish is the primary UI language — keep all user-facing text in Spanish
- Code identifiers (variables, functions) can be English or Spanish — follow existing patterns

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
1. Adding roles to `profiles` table instead of `user_roles`
2. Using localStorage for auth state
3. Hardcoding role checks instead of importing from `accessControl.ts`
4. Creating new Supabase client instances
5. Not checking mobile responsiveness
6. Using `any` types when proper types exist in `types/` folder
7. Direct color values instead of semantic design tokens
8. Skipping `useAuthenticatedQuery` for authenticated data fetching
